text: The canton of Melesse is an administrative division of the Ille-et-Vilaine department, in northwestern France. It was created at the French canton reorganisation which came into effect in March 2015. Its seat is in Melesse.Décret n° 2014-177 du 18 février 2014 portant délimitation des cantons dans le département d'Ille-et-Vilaine It consists of the following communes: #Clayes #Gévezé #Guipel #Hédé-Bazouges #Langouet #Melesse #La Mézière #Montreuil-le-Gast #Parthenay-de-Bretagne #Saint-Germain-sur-Ille #Saint- Gilles #Saint-Gondran #Saint-Médard-sur-Ille #Saint-Symphorien #Vignoc ==References== Category:Cantons of Ille-et-Vilaine
